It was an honor to be a part of the centennial services in remembrance of the Armistice of World War I at the Suresnes American Cemetery and Memorial and lay a wreath at the gravesite of a fallen Texan, U.S. Marine Corps Private Pete Reedy. https://flores.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=399126 …
I am so sorry to hear about the loss of this committed American Patriot.

This year, Veterans Day also marks the 100th anniversary of the Armistice of World War I – marking the end of “The Great War.” It is important that we honor the sacrifices of past generations on this day of remembrance. pic.twitter.com/nMmltQZfN3
